<H3> <TI>   Statement Denies Algerian `Good Offices' for Iraqi Ties </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Statement Denies Algerian `Good Offices' for Iraqi Ties </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1605133494 Kuwait KUNA in Arabic 1239 GMT 16 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1605133494 </F>
<F P=104>  Kuwait KUNA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] Tunis, 16 May (KUNA) -- The Embassy of the State 
of Kuwait in Tunis today denied that there are Algerian good 
offices for what is described as clearing the air between Kuwait 
and the Iraqi regime, on the occasion of a tour to the recent 
Maghreb countries by Shaykh Sabah al-Ahmad, first deputy prime 
minister and foreign minister of Kuwait. 
  In a statement, a copy of which was received by KUNA, the 
Embassy expresses "Kuwait's rejection of the attempt to link 
Shaykh Sabah al-Ahmad's tour and the message which the head of 
the Iraqi regime sent to the Algerian president." [passage 
omitted] The Embassy statement affirms that relations between 
the State of Kuwait and the Iraqi regime are ruled by 
international legal resolutions which Iraq must observe, instead 
of making open attempts to contain them and evade implementing 
them. 

</TEXT>

