<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Rabin To Demand 'Arafat's Written Commitment to Accord </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Rabin To Demand 'Arafat's Written Commitment to Accord </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Speech `Casts Doubts' </H4>

<F P=102> TA2305121894 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1200 GMT 23 
May 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2305121894 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Prime Minister Yitzhaq Rabin says he will demand 
from Yasir 'Arafat to reaffirm in writing his commitment to the 
peace agreement signed earlier this month. 'Oded Ben-'Ami, the 
prime minister's spokesman, said that 'Arafat's speech in 
Johannesburg casts doubts on his sincerity with regard to the 
peace agreement. Ben-'Ami noted that Israel will put off the 
negotiations on the second stage of the agreement with the 
Palestinians until the PLO consolidates its rule in Gaza and 
Jericho. 
  In response, PLO member Jamil al-Tarifi said that any delay 
in the implementation of the next stage of the autonomy will 
constitute a deviation from the agreement. 

