<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Rabin Orders Contingency Plans for Accord Violations </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Rabin Orders Contingency Plans for Accord Violations </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA2405112994 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1100 GMT 24 
May 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2405112994 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Prime Minister Yitzhaq Rabin has instructed the IDF 
[Israel Defense Forces] to draft contingency plans for possible 
violations of the agreement with the PLO, Deputy Chief of Staff 
Amnon Shahaq told the Knesset Foreign Affairs and Defense 
Committee. He added that 3,200 Palestinian policemen have so far 
arrived in Gaza and Jericho, some of them from Sudan and Iraq. 
Hamas [Islamic Resistance Movement] is not taking part in and 
is not cooperating with the Palestinian police, he said. 
  Our correspondent Hayim Hecht reports that Major General 
Shahaq briefed the committee about the investigation of Mustafa 
al-Dirani, a member of Hizballah in Lebanon, and noted he is a 
tough nut to crack. The deputy chief of staff assessed that 
al-Dirani's interrogation will yet continue for a long time. 

</TEXT>

