<H3> <TI>   PNA Chooses Financial Group to Manage Funds </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    PNA Chooses Financial Group to Manage Funds </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2405183394 Algiers Voice of Palestine in Arabic 1702 GMT 
24 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2405183394 </F>
<F P=104>  Algiers Voice of Palestine </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Palestinian National Authority [PNA] announced 
today that it had appointed Morgan Stanley Asset Management, 
MSAM, to manage the funds given to administer and develop the 
West Bank and the Gaza strip under the leadership of the PNA. 
  This institution, which manages funds estimated at 50 
billion 
dollars, is a subsidiary of the Stanley Morgan Group [as heard], 
a large financial institution that has offices in the world's 
main financial centers. 
  The PNA said that it had chosen this institution to help in 
reassuring the donor states and agencies that the funds they had 
given to the PNA for the administration and development of the 
West Bank and Gaza were being managed with complete transparency 
and in a proficient and professional way through one of the 
world's eminent financial institutions. 

</TEXT>

