<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Al-'Attas' To Form New Republic's Cabinet </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Al-'Attas' To Form New Republic's Cabinet </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN2405160994 Damascus SANA in Arabic 1545 GMT 24 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN2405160994 </F>
<F P=104>  Damascus SANA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Damascus, 24 May (SANA)--Haydar Abu-Bakr al-'Attas, 
who is entrusted with forming a cabinet in the Democratic 
Republic of Yemen which was declared in Aden, has denied the 
downfall of any city in the south. He stressed that no party 
has achieved victory over the other in the raging war. 
  In an interview with Radio L'Orient today, al-'Attas, who is 
now in London, said that he will leave for Aden soon to form a 
cabinet and to hold further consultations with the brothers in 
Aden. 
  Concerning President 'Ali Salim al-Bid's presence in 
Hadhramaut, al-'Attas said that Mr. al-Bid is inspecting some 
troops there. 
  Al-'Attas said: We should work to stop the shedding of more 
blood and to save what remains of the Yemeni national resources. 

</TEXT>

