<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   YSP Official Outlines Initiative To End Fighting </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    YSP Official Outlines Initiative To End Fighting </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2405211794 Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network in 
Arabic 2026 GMT 24 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2405211794 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Interview with Dr. 'Abd-al-'Aziz al-Dali, head of the </F>
Political and Foreign Relations Department of the Yemeni 
Socialist Party, by unidentified correspondent; place and date 
not given -- recorded] 
  [Text] [Correspondent] You were with us when we heard our 
colleague Mamduh Sa'd's interview with Dr. 'Abd-al-Karim 
al-Iryani. What is your response and how can the ongoing 
conflict in Yemen be contained? 
  [Al-Dali] Actually I believe that the starting point in 
resolving the worsening crisis represented by this ferocious war 
should be an immediate halt to the war. Afterward, we could 
disengage the forces and then sit and talk about anything or any 
issue. 
  [Correspondent] How can the fighting be stopped amid these 
reports and statements by the two sides? 
  [Al-Dali] The aggressor should order a halt to his 
aggressions against the southern and eastern governorates. The 
aggressor must stop his aggressions against the eastern and 
southern governorates. We have agreed on more than one occasion 
to halt the fighting and to accept mediation efforts, and to sit 
down for talks with our brothers, but the other side has refused 
and rejected more than one initiative to halt the fighting. He, 
the aggressor, has to stop the fighting. 
  [Correspondent] President 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih is very 
strongly opposed to your declaration of secession from unity. 
  [Al-Dali] We did not choose to proclaim a new state in the 
southern and eastern governorates at our own choosing; there 
were reasons and motives that prompted us to do so. 
  [Correspondent] In a few words, what would you say about the 
YSP's initiative? 
  [Al-Dali] An immediate cease-fire, withdrawing and 
disengaging the forces, and sitting down for talks without 
preconditions. 

</TEXT>

