<H3> <TI>   Radio Reports French Statement of Support for Unity </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Radio Reports French Statement of Support for Unity </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN2405175494 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
1700 GMT 24 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2405175494 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] France, through its foreign minister, has expressed 
its concern for the preservation of Yemeni unity. Asked by a 
Cairo radio correspondent about France's stand on the 
developments in Yemen, French Foreign Minister Alain Juppe said: 
As a general rule, France believes that the Yemen unity, rather 
than secession, constitutes a factor of stability. Therefore, 
we prefer that Yemen unity is respected. 

</TEXT>

