<F P=100> IRAQ </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kurdish Forces Report Casualties Inflicted on PUK </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kurdish Forces Report Casualties Inflicted on PUK </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2405204594 Tehran IRNA in English 2012 GMT 24 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2405204594 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Mahabad (West Azerbaijan Prov.), May 24, 
IRNA--Iraq's Kurdish Revolutionary Hizballah forces killed 17 
attackers of the Patriotic Union of Kurdistan [PUK] in Chuman 
and Galaleh regions over the past two days of fighting in 
northeastern Iraq. 
  According to a Kurdish Revolutionary Hizballah spokesman 
here 
Tuesday [24 May] two combatants of the Kurdish Islamic forces 
also lost their lives as a result of clashes with Jalal 
Talabani's PUK. The source said another 11 PUK forces also 
were shot dead in an attack by Hizballah in the Be'erge and 
Qasruk regions. 
  In related news from the Iranian city of Sanandaj, 11 PUK 
forces were killed by the Islamic Movement of Kurdistan (IMK) 
which managed to capture Sirvan camp, 5 kms off 
Halabja-Suleymaniya route on Monday. 
  A source close to IMK said its forces also succeeded in 
gaining control of the strategic Hiro village in Qal'e Dizeh of 
Suleymaniya in an attack made on PUK positions over the past two 
days. 
  The source said 15 other PUK forces, including PUK 
commander, 
Hassan Rasul Omar, were killed in two other attacks. 
  Earlier, PUK had acknowledged the death of Hassan Kavestani, 
one of its top members who fell in the battle with IMK forces a 
couple. [sentence as received] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

