<F P=100> SYRIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Chinese Communist Party Delegation Pays Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Chinese Communist Party Delegation Pays Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Chinese Delegation, ASBP Hold Talks </H4>

<F P=102> JN2405135394 Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network in 
Arabic 1115 GMT 24 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2405135394 </F>
<F P=104>  Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A round of talks was held at the National Command of 
the Arab Socialist Ba'th Party [ASBP] today between the ASBP 
delegation led by Comrade 'Abdallah al-Ahmar, ASBP assistant 
secretary general, and the delegation of the Chinese Communist 
Party, led by Comrade Wei Jianxing, member of the Political 
Bureau and head of the Chinese Federation of Trade Unions. 
  Attending the talks on the Syrian side were Comrade Mut'ib 
Shinan, ASBP National Command member, and 'Abdallah Abu-al-Rish, 
member of the Party Committee for Supervision and Inspection. 
On the Chinese side were members of the accompanying Chinese 
Communist Party delegation. 
  The talks dealt with the progress in relations of 
cooperation 
between the two friendly parties in accordance with the program 
signed between them in 1991. The two sides also reviewed the 
two parties' activities in their countries to continue the 
process of development and construction in order to achieve the 
objectives set by each party in its program of action to develop 
its country based on the independent option of the people. 
  The two sides also stressed the need to promote cooperation 
between the two parties in the interest of the two friendly 
peoples and countries. They also stressed the importance of 
consultation and coordination on all the international issues 
and developments of joint interest to both parties and countries. 
  The two sides also reviewed developments in the Arab and 
international arenas and in southeast Asia, and the current 
international developments' effects on international relations. 
The two sides stressed the importance of international 
cooperation to achieve world peace and security in a way to 
fulfill peoples' desire to safeguard their independence, to 
determine their future, and to affirm their independent option 
to develop their countries. 

</TEXT>

