<F P=100> ARAB AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Egypt </F>
<H3> <TI>   AL-AHRAM Urges Sudan To `Return to Logic' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    AL-AHRAM Urges Sudan To `Return to Logic' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2505071794 Cairo MENA in Arabic 0610 GMT 25 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2505071794 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 25 May (MENA) -- AL-AHRAM says the Sudanese 
Government, through its illogical measures against Egypt and its 
illegal confiscation of Egyptian property in Sudan, proves that 
it does not have the required level of political thinking and 
that it is exploiting Egypt's obvious tolerance, patience, and 
rational reaction to such measures. 
  The paper stresses in its editorial today that Egypt does 
not 
want to add a new crisis to those already experienced by the 
Arabs or erupting in their faces occasionally. Egypt believes 
that the Sudanese measures, although tactless, are too small and 
trivial to cause a serious crisis between Cairo and Khartoum. 
  This being so, the paper adds, the Sudanese Government 
should 
realize that Egypt's silence does not stem from weakness, its 
patience does not reflect a lack of will, and its failure to 
retaliate does not proceed from fear. 
  AL-AHRAM calls on the Sudanese Government to return to logic 
and understand the truth of Egypt's position and policy so that 
it may not take similar unwise and shortsighted measures in 
future. 
  The paper also urges the government in Khartoum to learn 
from 
the experience of insensible people here and there in the Arab 
world, which suffers the consequences of the foolish policies 
pursued by some of its leaders. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-60454 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drnes101_c_94004" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-NES-94-101 </AU>
