<H3> <TI>   Khartoum Summons Egyptian Ambassador </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Khartoum Summons Egyptian Ambassador </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2505072394 Cairo MENA in Arabic 0650 GMT 25 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2505072394 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Khartoum, 25 May (MENA) -- The Sudanese Foreign 
Ministry summoned Egyptian Ambassador to Sudan Dr. Hasan 
Jad-al-Haqq late last night to inform him of its protest over 
the two statements the Egyptian Foreign Ministry issued in 
reaction to the Sudanese authority's closure of some Egyptian 
establishments and homes in Sudan last Friday. 
  The Sudanese ministry claimed that these measures were 
within 
the context of enforcing the new Sudanese law on rents. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

