<F P=100> LEBANON </F>
<H3> <TI>   Al-Dirani Abduction Prompts Protest, Denunciations </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Al-Dirani Abduction Prompts Protest, Denunciations </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Complaint Lodged With UN </H4>

<F P=102> NC2405142094 Beirut Radio Lebanon in Arabic 1300 GMT 24 May 
94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2405142094 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Radio Lebanon </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Lebanon today lodged a protest with the UN Security 
Council against Israel for the kidnapping of Mustafa al-Dirani, 
the official in the faithful resistance, from his home in 
al-Biqa' on Saturday 21 May. 
  Foreign Minister Faris Buwayz clarified that the complaint 
does not yet request the Security Council to convene. He noted 
that Lebanon reserves the right to ask the Security Council to 
convene when necessary. Minister Buwayz described the 
kidnapping as an act of piracy that violates human rights and 
Lebanon's sovereignty, and attacks its security and stability. 
  REUTER cited a responsible official at the Foreign Ministry 
as saying that the Lebanese complaint also demands that Israel 
should quickly release al-Dirani and return him to Lebanon since 
this act is considered a violation of Lebanon's sovereignty and 
contradicts the trends toward peace in the region. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

