<F P=102>   NC2505102194 Kafr Killa Voice of the South in Arabic 0700 
GMT 25 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2505102194 </F>
<F P=104>  Kafr Killa Voice of the South </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] General Antoine Lahd, accompanied by Israeli 
North Region Commander General Yitzhaq Mordekhay, Ground Army 
Commander Emmanuel Saqr, and Liaison Unit Commander Gabi 
Ashkenazi, visited al-Bayyadah yesterday to wish a happy 'Id 
al-Adha to Druze religious leaders. General Lahd hoped the next 
year will bring happiness and peace and that all foreign armies, 
including the Israeli and Syrian armies, will withdraw from 
Lebanon. But he noted that the Israelis are deployed on a 
particular part of the Lebanese territory for their security 
needs. The objectives and motives of the Syrians are known to 
all. 
  Mordekhay offered his 'Id congratulations and said that the 
region is enjoying security, thanks to the efforts of its sons, 
especially members of the South Lebanese Army. He said the 
Israeli soldiers have been ordered to be careful after 
information that sabotage elements are trying to kidnap them. 
He said he currently has no information about any specific 
reaction by the sabotage organizations in Lebanon to the 
kidnapping of Mustafa al-Dirani. He said the Israeli Army is 
prepared for any eventuality. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

