</HEADER>

<F P=100> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   Saudi `Inefficiency' Blamed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Saudi `Inefficiency' Blamed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2505085594 Tehran IRNA in English 0428 GMT 25 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2505085594 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Mecca, May 24, IRNA -- Although eye-witnesses and 
hospital officials say a large number of pilgrims were trampled 
to death in a ceremony known as "stoning the devil" in Mina, 10 
kms east of Mecca Monday, Saudi Arabia has so far refused to 
disclose the number of casualties. 
  In a bid to acquit Saudi Arabia of any charges of negligence 
towards providing security for pilgrims, a government official 
at the Health Ministry announced Monday that 829 pilgrims had 
died in accidents or from old age and heat since May 12. 
Eye-witnesses blame yesterday's tragic event on the 
inefficiency of Saudi officials and their permission to [allow] 
small and large motor cars to move in the region. 
  There are contradictory reports of casualties released by 
representative offices of various countries in Mecca but none of 
them can be confirmed because of the lack of official statistics 
and Riyadh's silence on the issue. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

