<F P=105>  Persian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] President Hashemi-Rafsanjani today received Mr. 
Erwin Arrieta, the Venezuelan energy and mines minister. At the 
meeting, the Venezuelan energy and mines minister described the 
role of Iran's history and civilization in the civilization of 
the world as very valuable. He said: The expansion of warm 
cooperation with Iran based on mutual interests is very 
important for us. The grounds for expanding bilateral 
cooperation are plentiful. He described one of the aims of his 
visit to Iran, besides assessing the oil issue in the oil-rich 
countries of Asia, as making use of Iran's valuable experience 
in the sphere of mines and metals. 
  According to the Central News Unit, Mr. Hashemi-Rafsanjani, 
for his part, spoke of the activation of the mining sector 
during the first five-year plan, especially relating to iron 
ore, coal, refractory materials, copper, and aluminum mines. He 
said: Side by side with the mining sector, and in light of the 
high cost of transporting raw materials, the growth of the 
metallurgy sector is of special importance. Iran is ready to 
provide Venezuela with its expertise and experience in the 
fields of oil, gas, mining, the petrochemical industry, and 
metallurgy. 

</TEXT>

