<F P=105>  Persian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ways and means of strengthening OPEC were assessed 
in today's meeting between Mr. Erwin Arrieta, Venezuelan energy 
and mines minister, and Mr. Gholam Reza Aqazadeh, oil minister 
of the Islamic Republic of Iran. 
  According to the Central News Unit, the need for greater 
cooperation among OPEC members, in order to further mutual 
economic interests, was stressed at the meeting. 
  Mr. Aqazadeh reiterated that Venezuela and five 
oil-producing 
countries of the Persian Gulf currently control two thirds of 
oil reserves and 70 percent of exports. Despite the existence 
of different points of view, they could take joint steps toward 
the strengthening of OPEC, he said. 
  The Venezuelan mines and energy minister, who met Kuwaiti 
oil 
officials before meeting the oil officials of our country, has 
said that, in order to achieve better prices, his country 
supports a reduction in oil production. 

</TEXT>

