BFN 

  [Text] Mashhad, Khorasan Prov., May 22, IRNA -- The 
government was paying some 6,000 billion rials in subsidies on 
essential goods in the current year, Interior Minister 'Ali 
Mohammed Besharati announced here Sunday. 
  Speaking at a country wide gathering of political and 
security deputy governors general, Besharati added that some 
2,000 billion rials of subsidies has been allocated to bread and 
some 600 billion rials for pharmaceutics. 
  The two day seminar is to deal with security along the 
borders and drug trafficking. 
  In related news, the public relations office of the plan and 
budget organization announced today that the government was 
paying over 20,000 billion rials in subsidies on energy. 

