<H3> <TI>   Prime Minister Rao Concludes U.S. Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Prime Minister Rao Concludes U.S. Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Voices `Satisfaction' With Talks </H4>

<F P=102> BK2005153994 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 0830 
GMT 20 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2005153994 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi All India Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The prime minister has expressed satisfaction on 
his visit to the United States. Addressing a news conference in 
Washington D.C., Mr. Narasimha Rao said though essentially a 
goodwill mission, the visit has both political and economic 
content. His discussions with President Clinton had convinced 
him that India and the United States can develop bilateral 
relationship of maturity and strength. It can contribute not 
only to mutual good but also to the world as a whole. His 
current visit has helped towards developing better understanding 
between the two countries, Mr. Rao observed. 

</TEXT>

