<H3> <TI>   Prime Minister Rao Concludes U.S. Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Prime Minister Rao Concludes U.S. Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Minister Hails `Successful' Outcome </H4>

<F P=102> BK2305070794 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 1230 
GMT 22 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2305070794 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi All India Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The finance minister, Dr. Manmohan Singh, has said 
that the successful outcome of the Rao-Clinton summit has 
vindicated that the prime minister's visit to the United States 
was in the national interest. Speaking to reporters in London, 
he said both the U.S. Government and captains of American trade 
and industry have welcomed India's economic reforms program and 
the strategy integrating its economy with the global economy. 
Dr. Singh said there is a lot of enthusiasm in the United 
States about India's prospects as a large and emerging market 
offering great opportunities for American investments. 

</TEXT>

