<F P=102>   JN2405174094 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
1700 GMT 24 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2405174094 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Brother Lieutenant General 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih, 
chairman of the Presidential Council and supreme commander of 
the Armed Forces, has received a cable from the officers, NCO's, 
and soldiers of the (?al-Khurafi) camp, who used to be called 
the private guard of traitor 'Ali Salim al-Bid. The cable 
voices the congratulations of the officers, noncommissioned 
officers [NCO's], and soldiers to the brother leader president 
and supreme commander of the Armed Forces on the occasion of the 
blessed 'Id al-Adha and the fourth national anniversary of the 
Republic of Yemen and also expresses support for the forces of 
unity and legitimacy. 
  The cable condemns what was done by the gang of apostasy and 
secession in the Yemeni Socialist Party, led by traitor 'Ali 
Salim al-Bid, namely, the declaration of secession, stressing 
that it is considered high treason against the homeland, the 
unity, and the Yemeni people and that history will not forgive 
that gang's crimes against the people and the homeland. The 
officers, NCO's, and soldiers in the al-Khurafi camp expressed 
their great appreciation for the step the leadership has taken 
under brother LIt. Gen. 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih to preserve the 
homeland's unity and safeguard its gains, which were achieved 
for our people under the immortal Yemeni revolution. They also 
stressed their determination to defend unity under the Republic 
of Yemen. 

</TEXT>

