<H3> <TI>   Ba'th Party Statement Denounces `Secessionist Crime' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ba'th Party Statement Denounces `Secessionist Crime' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN2405155494 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
1519 GMT 24 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2405155494 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Unscheduled announcement"] </F>
  [Text] The Arab Socialist Ba'th Party has denounced the 
secessionist crime perpetrated by the misguided group dominating 
the [Yemeni] Socialist Party [YSP]. 
  A statement issued by the Yemen Command of the Arab 
Socialist 
Ba'th Party says: Our people and all their good forces have 
always pinned and are still pinning their hopes on the unionist 
current in the YSP to do something for the sake of beloved Yemen 
in order to entrench the Yemeni unity, adhere to constitutional 
legitimacy, confront secession, and to issue a principled reply 
