<H3> <TI>   Diplomat Said Expelled From U.S. for `Violations' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Diplomat Said Expelled From U.S. for `Violations' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN2605092194 Amman Radio Jordan in English 0900 GMT 26 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN2605092194 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman Radio Jordan </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Iraq's senior diplomat in Washington has been 
expelled for alleged violations of the agreement that allowed 
Iraq to maintain a diplomatic presence in the United States. 
THE WASHINGTON POST said that the diplomat had tried to lobby 
members of Congress and sent out news releases calling for an 
end to the United Nations economic embargo against his country. 
It said that he had also hired and fired staff without 
notifying the State Department or actions counter to the 
agreement. The paper said that the State Department did not 
announce his expulsion, but confirmed it when queried. 

</TEXT>

