<H3> <TI>   'Arafat Meets With Self-Rule Administration Members </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    'Arafat Meets With Self-Rule Administration Members </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2505235694 Rabat Moroccan Kingdom Radio Network in Arabic 
2300 GMT 25 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2505235694 </F>
<F P=104>  Rabat Moroccan Kingdom Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Palestinian President Yasir 'Arafat held a 
meeting with some members of the group entrusted with 
administering the self-rule in Gaza and Jericho in Tunis this 
evening. 
  Palestinian sources said that more than ten members of the 
group participated in the unofficial meeting, and that the other 
18 members concerned would arrive tomorrow in Tunis to take part 
in the first official meeting of the group during which they 
were expected to be sworn in and prepare the group's working 
program for the forthcoming period. 
  Palestinian sources had previously announced that tomorrow's 
meeting would also be distinguished by announcing the names of 
the remaining members of the self-rule administration group; the 
Cairo agreement on implementing self-rule stipulated that it 
would comprise 24 members. 

</TEXT>

