<H3> <TI>   Fatah, Organizations Call For Release of Yasin </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Fatah, Organizations Call For Release of Yasin </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2505191994 Algiers Voice of Palestine in Arabic 1702 GMT 
25 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2505191994 </F>
<F P=104>  Algiers Voice of Palestine </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A communique distributed in Gaza yesterday and 
signed by the Fatah Movement, captives movement [al-harakah 
al-asirah], and all the national and humanitarian organizations, 
said that the guardian [ra'i] sentenced to life imprisonment was 
suffering from paralysis of the right leg and a slipped disc 
after undergoing two surgical operations, with no progress in 
his state of health. The communique said that the guardian was 
in solitary confinement at the al-Ramlah prison and that he 
could die any at any moment. 
  The communique called on all human rights organizations in 
the world to intervene to put pressure on the Israeli Government 
to release all the prisoners and appealed to people of 
conscience to take serious actions to end the suffering and to 
secure the immediate release of Shaykh Ahmad Yasin, who is 
suffering from various ailments in addition to almost total 
paralysis. 
  Prisoners urged the population to stage sit-ins at the 
offices of the Red Cross, fly black flags, demand the release of 
the prisoners, and convey their demands to legal and 
international bodies. 

</TEXT>

