<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Russia's Posuvalyuk, DFLP's Hawatimah Meet </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Russia's Posuvalyuk, DFLP's Hawatimah Meet </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN2505194994 Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network in 
Arabic 1815 GMT 25 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2505194994 </F>
<F P=104>  Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Russian envoy Viktor Posuvalyuk today met with a 
Palestinian delegation led by Nayif Hawatimah, secretary general 
of the Democratic Front for the Liberation of Palestine [DFLP]. 
  During the meeting, they discussed the Palestinian situation 
and the successive developments in the wake of the signing of 
the Cairo agreement. The Russian envoy indicated the importance 
of the terms of reference for negotiations on the 
Palestinian-Israeli track, based on international legitimacy and 
its resolutions, in a way that secures the Palestinian people's 
right to establish an independent state and guarantee a just 
solution to the refugee issue. 
  For his part, Hawatimah said the Cairo agreement fragmented 
the Arab negotiation front and opened the way for separate and 
partial solutions that cannot achieve comprehensive peace and 
stability in the region. He indicated this agreement carries 
the elements of its own failure. 
  Hawatimah demanded the activation of the Russian role in the 
region in order to achieve the interests of the Arab and Russian 
peoples and bring about real peace. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

