<F P=100> Egypt </F>
<H3> <TI>   Sudan Continues To Seize Egyptian Properties </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Sudan Continues To Seize Egyptian Properties </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2505210494 Cairo MENA in Arabic 2010 GMT 25 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2505210494 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Khartoum, 25 May (MENA)--Dr. Hasan Jad al-Haqq, 
Egypt's ambassador in Khartoum, this evening held a celebration 
on the occasion of Africa Day during which he delivered 
President Muhammad Husni Mubarak's speech in his capacity as 
chairman of the OAU, in the presence of over 500 guests, 
including ambassadors and ranking accredited African and Arab 
figures in Khartoum. 
  The Sudanese Government's representative was noticeably 
absent from the celebration, despite the fact that the Sudanese 
Government was sent an invitation by the head of the African 
diplomatic corps. 
  Ugandan Ambassador to Sudan E. Obitre Gama, doyen of the 
African diplomatic corps in Khartoum, delivered a speech in 
which he condemned the measures taken by the Sudanese 
authorities against the Egyptian interests in Khartoum, such as 
the Egyptian Club, where the celebration was supposed to have 
been held. Because of this, the celebration was moved to the 
home of the Egyptian ambassador in Khartoum. 
  Ambassador Gama thanked Egypt and its ambassador for hosting 
this celebration and not cancelling it. This gave many Africans 
an opportunity to celebrate their day. 
  During the celebration, the Egyptian ambassador received 
notification from the head of the Egyptian Irrigation Department 
in Sudan that this evening the Sudanese authorities took control 
of another house of the Egyptian Irrigation Department in 
Khartoum, the resident of which is currently on annual leave in 
Cairo. This report drew condemnations from the sons of the 
African communities in Sudan who were attending the celebration. 
  Thus, the number of houses that have been occupied has risen 
to 14, in addition to the Egyptian Defense Office's three rest 
houses. 
  In a statement to the MENA correspondent in Khartoum, Dr. 
Hasan Jad-al-Haqq affirmed at the end of the celebration that no 
matter what happened, today's celebration of Africa Day was not 
going to be cancelled. He affirmed that he considers the 
residence of the Egyptian ambassador in Khartoum to be the home 
for all Africans in Sudan. 

</TEXT>

