<H3> <TI>   South Yemen's al-'Attas Arrives in Cairo </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    South Yemen's al-'Attas Arrives in Cairo </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2605064694 Cairo MENA in Arabic 2208 GMT 25 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2605064694 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 25 May (MENA) -- Haydar Abu-Bakr al-'Attas, 
the former Yemeni prime minister who was recently appointed 
prime minister of the South after it declared secession, arrived 
in Cairo tonight on a visit to Egypt as part of a tour of Arab 
countries. 
  In an arrival statement al-'Attas said he hoped to meet 
President Husni Mubarak tomorrow, Thursday. He said: I wish to 
take this opportunity to express my deep thanks to Egypt and its 
president for all the efforts to remove Yemen from this crisis. 
  He said that Egypt always plays a pioneering role in our 
Arab 
homeland and noted that during his visit to Cairo he will 
discuss the situation in Yemen, the war there, and the 
importance of stopping it as soon as possible. 
  Al-'Attas added that these topics will be discussed with 
Egyptian officials. He said he believed that they are fully 
informed of all the events in Yemen. He noted that various 
countries' recognition of the South of Yemen will be the topic 
of discussion during his talks. 

</TEXT>

