<H3> <TI>   Egypt Protests Actions Against `Interests, Property' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Egypt Protests Actions Against `Interests, Property' </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Egyptian Embassy Delivers Memorandum </H4>

<F P=102> NC2105183094 Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network in 
Arabic 1730 GMT 21 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2105183094 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Egyptian Embassy in Khartoum today delivered an 
official memorandum to the Sudanese Foreign Ministry protesting 
the actions taken by Sudanese authorities against Egyptian 
interests, property, and nationals in Sudan. 
  The memorandum calls on the Sudanese authorities to 
reconsider these measures to safeguard relations between the two 
countries and avoid the deterioration of Egyptian-Sudanese 
relations on bilateral and international levels. 

</TEXT>

