<F P=100> Sri Lanka </F>
<H3> <TI>   Parliament Extends State of Emergency </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Parliament Extends State of Emergency </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2205080694 Colombo Sri Lanka Broadcasting Corporation 
International Service in English 1045 GMT 20 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2205080694 </F>
<F P=104>  Colombo Sri Lanka Broadcasting Corporation 
International Service </F>

<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A one month's extension to the emergency was 
approved by a majority of 46 votes in the parliament yesterday. 
One hundred and two members voted for the motion while 56 
opposed it. Winding up the debate, Prime Minister Ranil 
Wickremesinghe said that the government is committed to 
establishing peace in the North and East. It has kept channels 
open for a negotiated settlement. The government is seeking to 
restore law and order throughout the island. The prime minister 
said that the Penal Code will be amended so that offenders could 
be brought to justice immediately. Mr. Wickremesinghe invited 
the opposition to suggest amendments to the code. 

</TEXT>

