<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Minister: 'Arafat Decree No Violation of Accord </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Minister: 'Arafat Decree No Violation of Accord </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA2605103494 Tel Aviv DAVAR in Hebrew 26 May 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> TA2605103494 </F>
<F P=104>  Tel Aviv DAVAR </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [ITIM report] </F>
  [Text] "The Palestinian Authority has the power to cancel 
previous legislation. This is no violation of the agreement." 
These remarks were made last night by Justice Minister David 
Liba'i in response to the decree by Yasir 'Arafat regarding the 
cancellation of the Israeli laws in Jericho. 
  Minister Liba'i added: "'Arafat tends to favor symbolic and 
demonstrative acts instead of coming down to the territories and 
starting to run the inhabitants' life and worrying over real 
needs. He did nothing by issuing a statement announcing that he 
is canceling the Israeli laws. According to the agreement 
between us, we have restricted the validity of their laws so 
that they cannot pass laws which contradict the agreement. He 
is no legislator, and has not presented an alternative or 
introduced order. All that he has done so far is make a 
statement." 
  The minister noted that the Palestinian Authority has the 
right to cancel some of the laws. It would not be a violation, 
he said, but the question is whether this is wise and how will 
it impact on the territory. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

