<H3> <TI>   Peres Holds Meetings With UNSC Members, Clinton </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Peres Holds Meetings With UNSC Members, Clinton </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Urges UNSC To Aid Palestinians </H4>

<F P=102> TA2405190294 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1800 GMT 24 
May 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2405190294 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Foreign Minister Shim'on Peres has called on the 
members of the UN Security Council [UNSC] to immediately send 
funds to the Palestinians. He noted that Israel continues 
paying the salaries of the Civil Administration workers in order 
to prevent a crisis, though they are not under Israeli 
jurisdiction. The foreign minister asked the Japanese 
ambassador to immediately provide the Palestinians with $30 
million of the $200 million his country pledged to give them. 
  Minister Peres met in New York with the ambassadors of the 
members of the UNSC. Our correspondent Arye Golan reports that 
the meeting was attended by the PLO's UN observer, and the 
ambassadors of Morocco and Djibouti. 

</TEXT>

