<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Salih Attends National Symposium in Sanaa </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Salih Attends National Symposium in Sanaa </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Symposium Emphasizes Allegiance </H4>

<F P=102> JN2605045094 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
0330 GMT 26 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2605045094 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The expanded national symposium attended by the 
leaderships of political parties and organizations, trade unions 
and mass and professional organizations; tribal chiefs and 
ulema; social figures, intellectuals and youth representatives; 
and all national forces and personages in all parts of the 
Yemeni homeland, ended in Sanaa last night. 
  The symposium issued a statement saying that the national 
symposium's pledge of allegiance to brother Lieutenant General 
'Ali 'Abdallah Salih, Presidential Council chairman, is a 
sincere pledge for the command of the battle for unity, for 
confronting secession, and for the march toward entrenching 
security and stability, and building a united Yemen which 
rejects partition, fragmentation, and the relinquishment of any 
inch of its territory--the Yemen of brotherhood, tolerance, and 
love. The symposium reiterated absolute condemnation and 
complete rejection of al-Bid's secessionist declaration and 
emphasized confrontation of the secessionists led by the traitor 
of the homeland, revolution, and nation, 'Ali Salim al-Bid. 
  The statement appealed to the Socialist Party leadership, 
cadres, and broad base which believe in unity and the homeland, 
to move fast and align with people's masses and political and 
national forces to face the threat and protect unity and 
constitutional legitimacy, and bury the crime of secession for 
ever. 
  The statement warned all states and regional and 
international organizations of the danger of dealing with the 
secessionist clique and said that the entire Yemeni people will 
regard such dealing as a flagrant hostile act against every 
Yemeni citizen and an interference in the internal affairs of 
the Republic of Yemen. The statement appealed to our Arab 
brothers and friends in the world, and all good men to rally 
round the Yemeni people, unity, progress, and stability. 

</TEXT>

