<H3> <TI>   Defense Minister Makes Appeal to `Misled' Forces </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Defense Minister Makes Appeal to `Misled' Forces </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN2605062394 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
0450 GMT 26 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2605062394 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Text" of an appeal by Defense Minister 'Abd-Rabbuh Mansur </F>
Hadi to the "misled" forces; date not given] 
  [Text] In the name of God, the merciful, the compassionate. 
Peace and blessing be upon His noble Prophet. To the misled and 
helpless brother officers, noncommissioned officers, and 
soldiers: O heroes of the Armed Forces--officers, NCO's, and 
soldiers: You have always been a symbol of national unity and a 
splendid example of national cohesion. You had the honor of 
taking the initiative to reunite the homeland. Therefore, you 
categorically rejected the instructions of the gangs of apostasy 
and secession and sided with the constitutional legitimacy, that 
is, with the people and the unity of the homeland. Therefore, a 
decree under Law No. 1 for 1994 was issued announcing a general 
amnesty in appreciation of these stands. 
  Consequently, the Defense Ministry has fixed the reception 
areas as follows: 
  1. The Aden axis. The brother officers, NCO's, and soldiers 
in the Aden Governorate should report to the units near their 
places in order to be sent to the military areas where they can 
perform their service. 
  2. The Lahij axis. The brother officers, NCO's, and 
soldiers should report to the units near their places in order 
to be sent to the military areas where they can perform their 
service. 
  3. All shall enjoy all rights and duties enjoyed by others 
in the Yemeni Armed Forces in accordance with the 
above-mentioned decree. 
  4. We appeal to all to respond and benefit from the sympathy 
and tolerance expressed by the decree toward the misled and 
helpless ones by joining the forces of legitimacy in order to 
form one unified army that fights bravely and faithfully for the 
sake of the people and homeland. 
  It is God who grants us guidance and success. 
  [Signed] Staff Brigadier General 'Abd-Rabbuh Mansur Hadi, 
minister of defense 

</TEXT>

