<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   YSP Officials' Families Reportedly Fleeing Country </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    YSP Officials' Families Reportedly Fleeing Country </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN2605065494 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
0500 GMT 26 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2605065494 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Yemeni News Agency, SABA', has learned from 
reliable sources reached by telephone in Djibouti that the 
family of Muhammad 'Ali al-Qayrahi, one of the secessionist 
leaders in the Yemeni Socialist Party [YSP], and families of 
some other YSP officials, had arrived in Djibouti three days 
ago. The sources added that as part of the exodus from Aden to 
Djibouti, a Russian ship carrying a number of families, 
including the families of some officials implicated in the 
secessionist plot led by YSP rebels against legitimacy, headed 
by traitor 'Ali Salim al-Bid, arrived at Djibouti port 
yesterday. The sources said the quarters that receive and 
accommodate these families deliberately disembarked some 
ordinary passengers and families from the ship for camouflage 
purposes and kept the families of ranking YSP figures on the 
ship until darkness as a security precaution and for fear of 
their being identified. 
  The secessionist, mutinous leaders are sending their 
families 
abroad, leaving the Aden people and their families as well as 
the misled and helpless ones in the Armed Forces to face dangers 
alone and serve as human shields to secure these leaders' escape 
and reunion with their families after having become certain that 
Aden's fall is imminent and that they will fall into the hands 
of the forces of unity and legitimacy. 

</TEXT>

