<H3> <TI>   Southern Official: Salih-al-Bid Meeting Possible </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Southern Official: Salih-al-Bid Meeting Possible </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN2505133594 Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network in 
Arabic 1115 GMT 25 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2505133594 </F>
<F P=104>  Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] [passage omitted] 'Abd-al-Ghani Makkawi, leader 
of the Yemeni National Grouping, has said unity cannot be 
imposed by the force of arms. He noted that reconciliation and 
dialogue are the basis for any solution in Yemen. 
  In an interview published by al-Shariqah AL-KHALIJ today, 
Makkawi said the Document of Pledge and Accord remains the ideal 
formula to achieve stability in the country. 
  Makkawi, who was appointed a member of the Presidential 
Council in the declared Democratic Republic of Yemen, said 
ending the military operations hinges on the will of President 
'Ali 'Abdallah Salih, noting that these operations cannot 
achieve a final solution to the situation unless the northern 
army turns into an occupation army, which is unacceptable and 
out of question. 
  Makkawi hinted at the possibility of a meeting between 
President Salih and 'Ali Salim al-Bid in Paris soon. He said: 
If agreement is reached to avoid the negative aspects that 
accompanied the declaration of unity, then results will be 
promising. 

</TEXT>

