<H3> <TI>   Former South President Condemns Decision To Secede </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Former South President Condemns Decision To Secede </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM2505140094 London AL-HAYAH in Arabic 24 May 94 pp 1, 4 </F>
<F P=103> PM2505140094 </F>
<F P=104>  London AL-HAYAH </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Ibrahim Humaydi: "'Ali Nasir Tells AL-HAYAH: </F>
Secession Decision Foolish"] 
  [Excerpts] Damascus -- Former South President 'Ali Nasir 
Muhammad yesterday vehemently attacked 'Ali Salim al-Bid, 
secretary general of the Yemeni Socialist Party, for announcing 
secession. He described the decision as "foolish." He stressed 
that he had turned down an offer from al-Bid to hold the post of 
deputy chairman of the presidential council in the "Democratic 
Republic of Yemen." [passage omitted] 
  'Ali Nasir said that he had requested al-Bid to "abandon the 
decision to secede and to return to dialogue" with Lieutenant 
General 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih, "because secession will not solve 
the problem." [passage omitted] 
  'Ali Nasir still believes that the "Pledge and Accord 
Document" signed in Amman in February "represents a base for 
solving all problems and contains comprehensive solutions to the 
crisis." He added that my return to Yemen "in these conditions 
is not my current concern. My concern is to bring an end to the 
fighting." 

</TEXT>

