<H3> <TI>   Cites `Initiative' To End Crisis </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Cites `Initiative' To End Crisis </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2605060194 Cairo MENA in Arabic 2235 GMT 25 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2605060194 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Damascus, 25 May (MENA)--Former Yemeni President 
'Ali Nasir Muhammad has praised the efforts exerted by Arab 
leaders, primarily President Husni Mubarak, King Fahd 
Bin-'Abd-al-'Aziz, and Shaykh Zayid Bin-sultan, to contain the 
Yemeni crisis. 
  Speaking to a MENA correspondent in Damascus tonight, the 
former Yemeni president said that he and several Yemeni figures 
are holding consultations to stop things deteriorating in Yemen, 
achieve a cease-fire, reverse the south Yemeni decision to 
secede, and start negotiations. The new initiative, he added, 
also aims to lift the siege on several Yemeni cities, preserve 
unity, and end the bloodshed. 

</TEXT>

