  [Text] Foreign Minister Faruq al-Shar' today received 
Viktor Posuvalyuk, Russian President Boris Yeltsin's envoy. 
  Attending the meeting were Dr. Ghassan Raslan, director of 
the East Europe Department at the Foreign Ministry, and 
Aleksandr Zotov, Russian ambassador in Damascus. 
  The talks dealt with developments in the peace process, 
Israel's arrogant policies, and its stands obstructing the 
achievement of a just and comprehensive peace in the region. 
The talks also dealt with relations between Syria and Russia 
and means of promoting them. 

