<H3> <TI>   Aircraft To Be Purchased From Central Asian States </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Aircraft To Be Purchased From Central Asian States </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK1905113194 Lahore JANG in Urdu 17 May 94 p 3 </F>
<F P=103> BK1905113194 </F>
<F P=104>  Lahore JANG </F>
<F P=105>  Urdu </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Editorial: "Decision To Purchase Aircraft from Central </F>
Asian States"] 
  [Text] According to a press report, Pakistan is drawing up 
a plan to purchase aircraft from Central Asian states as its Air 
Force is in need of fighter planes expeditiously. India's 
stepped up war preparations have intensified this need. 
Although negotiations are under way for the purchase of French 
aircraft, it might take three to four years to give effect to 
the talks and the changes taking place at the international and 
regional level are so rapid that there is no room for any 
complacency in the country's defense matters. For quite some 
time, Pakistan has been steadfast in its policy to purchase more 
and more weapons from the United States and we have suffered its 
repercussions through the three wars forced on us. The program 
formulated by the present government by deviating from its 
traditional path to purchase aircraft for its Air Force from 
Central Asian States is an important step taken in the right 
direction and no effort should be spared to remove all the 
bottlenecks on its way. 

</TEXT>

