<F P=101> India </F>
<H3> <TI>   Russia To Deliver First Cryogenic Engine in 1996 </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Russia To Deliver First Cryogenic Engine in 1996 </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2605103594 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 0830 
GMT 26 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2605103594 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi All India Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Russia will deliver the first of the seven 
cryogenic engines it is to supply to India in 1996. This was 
disclosed by the Russian first deputy foreign minister, Mr. 
Anatoliy Adamishin, in an interview to UNI TV during his visit 
to New Delhi recently. Mr. Adamishin, however, said under the 
terms of the recent agreement the technology for the cryogenic 
engines will not be transferred to India. He said India and 
Russia are likely to sign a comprehensive agreement on 
cooperation in the field of space technology during the 
forthcoming visit of the Indian prime minister to Russia. In 
reply to a question, Mr. Adamishin said Russia has been 
supplying spares for India's defense equipment. He said the two 
countries are discussing a proposal to set up joint ventures to 
manufacture military spares. 

</TEXT>

