<H3> <TI>   Ra'd-7 Military Operation Ends in Shiraz </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ra'd-7 Military Operation Ends in Shiraz </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2505091894 Tehran IRNA in English 0631 GMT 25 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2505091894 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tehran, May 25, IRNA -- The grand `Ra'd 7' (Thunder) 
military exercise ended in Darengon region of Shiraz, in 
southern Fars Province, Wednesday [25 May] morning in the 
presence of senior military officials. The military exercise 
was launched on May 22, marking the 12th anniversary of the 
liberation of the port city of Khorramshahr from Iraqi 
occupation. 
  Acting Commander of the Ground Forces General Karim Ebadat 
while inspecting the maneuver told IRNA that the military 
exercise was aimed at increasing the combat power of the forces. 
Various infantry and artillery units of the army, equipped with 
light and heavy weapons, participated in the military exercise. 

</TEXT>

