  [Excerpts] Khartoum, 22 May (SUNA) -- The government 
delegation to peace talks in Nairobi with the rebel factions 
arrived in Khartoum on Sunday [22 May] morning. Mr. Muhammad 
al-Amin Khalifah, speaker of the Transitional National Assembly 
[TNA] and head of the delegation to the peace talks, confirmed 
that the government is seriously committed to achieving a just 
and long-lasting peace with the rebel movement at the next round 
of talks, scheduled to be held on 18 July. 
  Mr. Khalifah told reporters upon arrival at Khartoum airport 
that the current round of talks was designed to discuss basic 
issues of the conflict, but the delay by three days of the 
arrival of the rebel factions prevented a detailed examination 
of these issues. [passage omitted] Mr. Khalifah stressed the 
need for contacts to continue between the government and the 
rebel movement, as that is the way to consolidate confidence 
between the two sides. [passage omitted] 

