<H3> <TI>   Zayid Renews Appeal to Salih To End Fighting </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Zayid Renews Appeal to Salih To End Fighting </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN2505072194 Manama WAKH in Arabic 0620 GMT 25 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN2505072194 </F>
<F P=104>  Manama WAKH </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Abu Dhabi, 24 May (WAKH) -- United Arab Emirates 
[UAE] President His Highness Shaykh Zayid Bin-Sultan Al Nuhayyan 
has received a phone call [word indistinct] from Yemeni 
President 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih. 
  The Emirates News Agency said discussions dealt with current 
developments and the bloody confrontation between brothers in 
Yemen. 
  Shaykh Zayid renewed his appeal to the Yemeni president to 
immediately stop fighting and avoid further shedding of Yemeni 
blood because what is going on is a disaster [words indistinct] 
Yemeni people who are suffering destruction to their property 
and national achievements. 
  His highness said that he is pained and saddened for every 
drop of Arab blood shed anywhere in the Arab world. He called 
for resorting to reason and logic, and for giving priority to 
the interests of Yemen and the Yemeni people. 
  His highness emphasized that the use of force will not lead 
to unity, and unity cannot be imposed by weapons but through 
understanding and agreement between the parties because the 
language of force and military means to resolve differences are 
rejected and do not serve sisterly Yemen. 

</TEXT>

