<F P=100> SOUTH ASIA </F>
<F P=101> India </F>
<H3> <TI>   Rao Encourages Private Investment in Power Sector </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Rao Encourages Private Investment in Power Sector </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2305160894 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 0830 
GMT 23 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2305160894 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi All India Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The prime minister said that the government will go 
all out to promote private investment in the power sector so 
that scarce resources are available for the social sector. He 
said many rules and regulations inhibiting private investment in 
the power sector have been removed in the last two years and the 
government is ready to further simplify the rules. Mr. 
Narasimha Rao was inaugurating a conference in New Delhi today 
titled India Power 94 on the development and financing of 
private sector power projects. He said the government is fully 
alive to the key role that power generation can play in the 
country's industrial growth. He urged the power sector to reach 
out to the people in the far-flung areas. 
  Earlier, in his keynote address, the power minister, Mr. 
N.K.P. Salve, said the center is awaiting the findings of the 
Sharad Pawar Committee on the working of state electricity 
boards. He said the two-tier price mechanism for the private 
power sector is proving highly encouraging. 

</TEXT>

