<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Induction of Fatah Hawks Into Police Denied </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Induction of Fatah Hawks Into Police Denied </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA2705103294 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 0900 GMT 27 
May 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2705103294 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Palestinians have announced that they do not 
intend to induct into the police force Fatah Hawks and wanted 
men who are not sanctioned by Israel. Our Army affairs 
correspondent Karmela Menashe reports that Brigadier General 
Yom-Tov Sami', the liaison with the Palestinians, sought to 
check reports that Uri Magidish's assassins had been inducted 
into the Palestinian police. He was told that Fatah Hawks had 
been concentrated in a classification camp, and that those who 
are found to be qualified to be policemen would be inducted only 
after Israel approves it. 
  Meanwhile, it has been learned that the policeman who banned 
Brig. Gen. Doron Almog from traveling freely on roads in the 
Gaza Strip has been brought to trial and sent to jail. IDF 
[Israel Defense Forces] sources this morning expressed 
satisfaction about the way Palestinian police roadblocks 
checking Palestinians at the border crossings with Israel have 
been working. 

</TEXT>

