<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Inter-Arab Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Al-Bid's Envoy Requests Reinstatement in League </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Al-Bid's Envoy Requests Reinstatement in League </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2605133294 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1240 GMT 26 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2605133294 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 26 May (MENA)--'Ali Salim al-Bid's envoy 
Engineer Haydar Abu-Bakr al-'Attas today asked Arab League 
Secretary General Dr. 'Ismat 'Abd-al-Majid to reinstate south 
Yemen's membership in the Arab League. 
  Following his meeting with Dr. 'Abd-al-Majid this afternoon, 
al-'Attas stated that the issue of reinstating south Yemen will 
be added to the agenda of the League's ministerial council. He 
added that he requested the League's support in tackling the 
Yemeni situation. He noted that his current tour of Arab states 
aims to discuss the recognition of the new situation in Yemen 
and returning the situation to what it was before May 1990, the 
date on which unity was declared between the two sectors of 
Yemen. 
  Dr. 'Abd-al-'Aziz al-Dali, member of the Yemeni Socialist 
Party's political bureau, who attended the meeting, expects 
several Arab states to recognize the Democratic Republic of 
Yemen soon. He said Dr. al-'Attas will tour the Gulf states 
after his visit to Cairo. 
  Al-Dali believes it is unlikely north Yemen will end the 
ongoing military battles to its advantage. He also denied that 
south Yemen received military assistance from any Arab or 
foreign state. 

</TEXT>

