<H3> <TI>   Arab Maghreb Union Urges Halt to Fighting in Yemen </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Arab Maghreb Union Urges Halt to Fighting in Yemen </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2605171494 Algiers Radio Algiers Network in Arabic 1600 
GMT 26 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2605171494 </F>
<F P=104>  Algiers Radio Algiers Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Joint" statement issued by the AMU Presidency; place and </F>
date not given -- live or recorded] 
  [Text] The AMU states -- Tunisia, Algeria, Libya, Morocco, 
and Mauritania -- have been following with great concern the 
serious developments in Yemen. The mass destruction resulting 
from the fighting between brothers -- for which the brotherly 
Yemeni people, above all, are paying the price -- is awakening 
the Arab and Islamic conscience with its ugliness. 
  The AMU states -- while warning yet again of the risks of 
this escalation that will harm the brotherly Yemeni people's 
gain of unity, in addition to the disastrous repercussions on 
peace and stability in the region that will result -- again urge 
all the Yemeni brothers to immediately halt the bloody 
confrontation, to return to reason, and to act in a spirit of 
responsibility, so that the way is cleared for dialogue on a 
peaceful settlement to the crisis in order that history may 
record it for the faithful sons of Yemen. 

</TEXT>

