<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Saudi Arabia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Minister on Need To Repulse `Unfair Allegations' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Minister on Need To Repulse `Unfair Allegations' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2505134494 Riyadh SPA in English 1248 GMT 25 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2505134494 </F>
<F P=104>  Riyadh SPA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Jeddah, May 25, SPA -- The minister of information, 
'Ali al-Sha'ir held a reception party on Tuesday [24 May] night 
to honour heads and members of the information delegations who 
came from various parts of the Arab and Islamic world to cover 
events of the just concluded haj season. The occasion was 
attended by Dr Fu'ad al-Farisi, undersecretary of the Ministry 
for Information Affairs, Ahmad al-Katani, under-secretary and 
general supervisors of the minister's office, Dr Shihab Jamjum, 
undersecretary for foreign information and senior officials of 
the ministry. 
  Addressing the gathering, minister al-Sha'ir welcomed the 
newsmen and conveyed to them the greetings of custodian of the 
two holy mosques, King Fahd Bin-'Abd-al-'Aziz and Crown Prince 
'Abdallah Bin-'Abd-al-'Aziz and congratulated them on completion 
of the haj rituals. 
  Referring to the current Arab and Islamic causes and the 
best 
means to promote them through various media means, minister 
al-Sha'ir cited the noble meanings included in the royal speech 
delivered by King Fahd and Crown Prince 'Abdallah to the Muslim 
nation during the annual reception ceremony held in Mina last 
Sunday on the best ways to face up seditions, conflicts and 
challenges engulfing the Arab and Muslim worlds and he reminded 
the newsmen on their national and Islamic duty to repulse such 
hostile and unfair allegations. 
  He recalled a speech he delivered during the last year's 
reception party in which he tackled the hostile and fierce media 
campaigns waged by some malicious and spiteful parties against 
the Islamic faith, some Islamic states and people in a desperate 
attempt to insult them, proposals for working out an 
informational method on basis of the information charter of 
honour with the aim for facing up the biased and false 
allegations against the nation and some Islamic states. 
  Al-Sha'ir expressed delight over the successful efforts made 
during the year to realise the noble purpose and thanked all 
fair writers and journalists who tried to confront the hostile 
campaigns. 
  Al-Sha'ir urged the members of the delegations to have a 
close look on the giant and brilliant achievements accomplished 
by the government of custodian of the two holy mosques, King 
Fahd Bin-'Abd-al-'Aziz and Crown Prince 'Abdallah 
Bin-'Abd-al-'Aziz at the grand mosque and nearby holy places in 
the holy city of Mecca and the blessed mosque of the prophet in 
Madina which were completed in a record span to convey what they 
have seen to their peoples. 
  He expressed thanks and appreciation to the various Saudi 
information bodies and personnel who took part in the coverage 
of the events of the haj and thanked Arab and Islamic brothers 
who participated in transmission of the haj rituals through 
radio and television networks for the outside world. 
  The gathering was also addressed by Amin Basyuni, chairman 
of 
trustees council of the Egyptian Radio and Television 
Federation, Qurban Alesen, the deputy information minister of 
turkmenstan who was speaking on behalf of the Asian Islamic 
states, Khero Zain, the head of the Indonesian information 
delegation, Mohammed al-Hadi al-Teraiki, director general of the 
Tunisian news agency who all highlighted the distinguished 
preparations made by the kingdom, under the leadership of King 
Fahd, for the haj season and the great services and facilities 
made for the comfort and security of pilgrims. 
  They also cited with appreciation the great efforts being 
made by custodian of the two holy mosques, King Fahd 
Bin-'Abd-al-'Aziz to realise Islamic solidarity and constructive 
cooperation under the umbrella of the Islamic teachings and his 
constant efforts to serve the Muslims, their sancturies and just 
causes on all regional and international forums. 
  On the other hand, the information delegations which 
participated in this haj season, expressed the heartfelt 
congratulations to King Fahd, Crown Prince 'Abdallah, the Saudi 
people on the occasion of the successful end of this haj season 
and Eid al-Adha. They cited with gratification to the marvelous 
expansion and development projects implemented at the holy 
places in Mecca and Madina as a civilized landmark of the era of 
custodian of the two holy mosques, King Fahd Bin-'Abd-al-'Aziz. 
They also thanked the Saudi concerned authorities for the 
comfortable means and integrated services rendered for all 
pilgrims. 

</TEXT>

