<F P=106> [Presidential Decree No. 26 issued in Sanaa on 26 May] </F>
  [Text] The Presidential Council chairman, 
  After taking cognizance of the Republic of Yemen 
Constitution, at the recommendation of the acting prime 
minister, in accordance with the requirements of the public 
interest, and following the approval of the Presidential 
Council, decides: 
<H5>  Article One: The following brothers shall be appointed to </H5>
the Council of Ministers in the posts appearing opposite their 
names. 
  1. 'Abd-al-Qadir 'Abd-al-Rahman Ba Jammal, deputy prime 
minister 
  2. Faysal 'Uthman Bin-Shamlan, minister of oil and 
mineral resources 
  3. Ahmad Musa'id Husayn 
<H5>  Article Two: This decree shall go into effect as of the </H5>
date of its publication. It shall be published in the official 
gazette. 
  Issued at the Presidential Office in Sanaa on 17 Dhi 
al-Hijjah 1414 Hegira, corresponding to 26 May 1994 
  [Signed] Lieutenant General 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih, 
Presidential Council chairman; Dr. Muhammad Sa'id al-'Attar, the 
acting prime minister 

