<H3> <TI>   Al-Iryani on Civil War, YSP, Solution to Crisis </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Al-Iryani on Civil War, YSP, Solution to Crisis </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Claims Saudi Involvement in Supplying Arms </H4>

<F P=102> LD2605152494 Tripoli Great Jamahiriyah Radio Network in 
Arabic 1230 GMT 26 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2605152494 </F>
<F P=104>  Tripoli Great Jamahiriyah Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] The Yemeni civil service minister and member of 
the General People's Congress in brotherly Yemen affirmed the 
Yemeni people's appreciation of the brother leader of the 
revolution's firm and unwavering stance in support of the unity 
of the Arab nation and the freedom of the Arab people. 
  In an interview with AL-ZAHF AL-AKHDAR, the Yemeni civil 
service minister said that the leader Mu'ammar al-Qadhdhafi had 
made great efforts toward achieving Yemeni unity. [passage 
omitted] 
  For his part, Yemeni Planning Minister 'Abd-al-Karim 
al-Iryani announced yesterday that Yemenis living in Saudi 
Arabia had sent large sums of money to the forces of the 
splinter group within the Socialist Party in southern Yemen 
headed by 'Ali Salim al-Bid for the purchase of weapons and 
military supplies from abroad. 
  In a statement to journalists, he indicated that Saudi 
Arabia 
was involved in this, explaining that a military consignment 
worth 5 million dollars was purchased for the rebels in the 
south by one of the Yemenis resident in Saudi Arabia. He said 
that the consignment was now being detained at a Red Sea port in 
Djibouti. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

