<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   'Abd-al-Ghani on Military Situation, YSP, Talks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    'Abd-al-Ghani on Military Situation, YSP, Talks </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    On Scud Attack, Settlement Prospects </H4>

<F P=102> PM2605114594 London AL-HAYAH in Arabic 25 May 94 pp 1, 4 </F>
<F P=103> PM2605114594 </F>
<F P=104>  London AL-HAYAH </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Interview with 'Abd-al-'Aziz 'Abd-al-Ghani, member of the </F>
Yemeni Presidential Council and assistant secretary general of 
the General People's Congress, by unidentified correspondent in 
Sanaa; date not given] 
  [Text] [AL-HAYAH] How will you reply to the Scud missile 
fired on residential areas in the center of Sanaa Monday [23 
May] evening? 
  ['Abd-al-Ghani] That was a criminal and cowardly act 
perpetrated by the gang of apostasy and secession within the 
Socialist Party leadership. This is in addition to the previous 
criminal acts. They fired their missiles on residential areas. 
The last missile was fired on a hospital. We can see how they 
are continuing to pursue their destructive policy. While we 
continue to pursue our constructive policy for rebuilding and 
development. There is, of course, a difference between the two 
lines -- a difference which ordinary citizens can see. Their 
criminal acts will not pass without punishment, and our people 
know how to respond to these people. 
  [AL-HAYAH] What will be the punishment? 
  ['Abd-al-Ghani] The punishment that every criminal who kills 
innocent people deserves. 
  [AL-HAYAH] Does that mean you will continue your military 
pressure on the other side? 
  ['Abd-al-Ghani] Our military actions against the leadership 
of the rebels and secessionists in the Socialist Party will not 
be suspended until Yemen's unity returns solid and without these 
secessionists. 
  [AL-HAYAH] Now that government forces have seized 'Ataq, the 
axis of the central sector of southern governorates, will they 
advance toward Hadhramaut? 
  ['Abd-al-Ghani] Military actions against these people will 
not be suspended in any area until the people get rid of them. 
  [AL-HAYAH] Is there a political solution to this war and the 
current problem? 
  ['Abd-al-Ghani] A political solution is on the cards when 
military operations cease and the 16 leaders of the secession 
gang, whose prosecution has been ordered by the prosecutor 
general, give themselves up. 
  [AL-HAYAH] We understand that the priority now is the 
military battle and the destruction of your rivals. 
  ['Abd-al-Ghani] The fighting was started by the secessionist 
gang in the Socialist Party, and we are defending unity against 
what these secessionists are doing. 
  [AL-HAYAH] Will the Socialist Party and some of its leaders 
whom you consider moderate have a role in the future of the 
political movement and power in Yemen? 
  ['Abd-al-Ghani] We are willing to talk with Socialist Party 
members who have not participated in the secession crime. 
  [AL-HAYAH] It has been noted that the prosecution and arrest 
warrant issued by the prosecutor general in Sanaa against 16 
Socialist Party leaders does not include the names of important 
Socialist Party leaders like Salim Salih Muhammad, the party's 
assistant secretary general; Dr. Yasin Sa'id Nu'man, chairman of 
the party's Secretariat; and Dr. 'Abd-al-'Aziz al-Dali, chairman 
of the party's external relations department. Does that mean 
that it is possible to engage in a dialogue with these? 
  ['Abd-al-Ghani] We are willing to engage in a dialogue with 
all the Socialist Party leaders who have not participated in the 
secessionist operation. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-60649 </DOCNO>
