<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   'Abd-al-Ghani on Military Situation, YSP, Talks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    'Abd-al-Ghani on Military Situation, YSP, Talks </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Rules Out UAE's Recognition of South </H4>

<F P=102> JN2505175494 Paris Radio Monte Carlo in Arabic 1710 GMT 25 
May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2505175494 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris Radio Monte Carlo </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Regarding the Arab stand vis-a-vis the Yemeni 
southerners' secession declaration and the proclamation of an 
independent state, 'Abd-al-'Aziz 'Abd-al-Ghani, member of the 
Yemeni Presidential Council, told told our radio correspondent 
Ahmad Birru: 
  [Begin 'Abd-al-Ghani recording] In fact, we do not believe 
that the United Arab Emirates [UAE] has recognized the 
secessionist state or the secession declaration announced by 
'Ali Salim al-Bid. The UAE has always been with unity, 
particularly Shaykh Zayid Bin-Sultan, who supported Yemen unity. 
We do not believe any Arab or foreign state will recognize this 
secession declaration announced by 'Ali Salim al-Bid, because it 
is unconstitutional. 
  We do not want to impose unity by force, but (?through 
peaceful means). The whole Yemeni people in the southern, 
eastern, northern, and western governorates support unity. 
Those who are imposing state authority in the southern 
governorates are government forces. These forces are not from 
the northern governorates, but from northern and southern 
governorates. The northern governorates are not imposing unity 
on the southern governorates. There is readiness for unity. As 
it was achieved peacefully, it will continue so. All the Yemeni 
people support unity. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-60650 </DOCNO>
