<H3> <TI>   Official Praises Libyan Leader's Initiative </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Official Praises Libyan Leader's Initiative </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2605223894 Tripoli JANA in English 1449 GMT 26 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2605223894 </F>
<F P=104>  Tripoli JANA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tripoli, Al Maa'[May] 26, JAMAHIRIYAH NEWS AGENCY -- 
'Abd-al-'Aziz al Dali, the chairman of the Foreign Relations 
Committee in the Socialist Party in Yemen has highly praised the 
initiative undertaken by the leader of the revolution to defuse 
the tragic events in the Yemen. 
  In statements to the Jamahiriyah News Agency, the official 
applauded the sincere efforts exerted by the leader to initiate 
action to bring an end to the fighting between fellow Yemenis. 
  The chairman of the Foreign Relations Committee in the 
Yemeni 
Socialist Party addressed a letter of gratitude and appreciation 
to the leader for his unswerving pro-unity and pro-nationalist 
stance. 
  The chairman said that the efforts exerted by the Great 
Jamahiriyah to bring a swift end to the suffering of the Yemeni 
people and prevent further bloodshed was greatly appreciated and 
welcomed by all Yemenis. 
  The chairman applauded the Great Jamahiriyah's concern for 
the security and stability of the Yemeni people and for 
preventing an escalation of the fighting. 
  In statements given elsewhere, Al Dali said that he would be 
meeting today with Dr. Esmat 'Abd-al-Meguid, the secretary 
general of the Arab League where he will inform him of latest 
developments of the current situation in the Yemen saying that 
the secessionists who declared the breakaway Democratic Republic 
of Yemen in the south, had submitted an application for 
membership to the Arab League. 

</TEXT>

