<H3> <TI>   Military Operations, Battle Progress Reported </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Military Operations, Battle Progress Reported </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    South Reports Missile Attack on Aden </H4>

<F P=102> EA2605163994 Aden Democratic Republic of Yemen Radio Network 
in Arabic 1400 GMT 26 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA2605163994 </F>
<F P=104>  Aden Democratic Republic of Yemen Radio Network 
in Arabic 1400 GMT 26 May 94 </F>

<F P=105> Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] A responsible source in the Command of the Armed 
Forces of the Democratic Republic of Yemen [DRY] has condemned 
the dangerous escalation in the war by the gang of the bloody 
al-Ahmar clan in Sanaa which launched four missiles on the city 
of Aden early this morning. The calm and peaceful inhabitants 
of Aden were taken by surprise by these four missiles, at a time 
when the adventurist gang in Sanaa is shouting about its wish to 
bring about a solution by way of a cease-fire. This shows not 
only the insincerity of this bloody gang, but also once again 
confirms its insistence on persevering with the destructive war 
against our people in the DRY and with the lack of care for the 
innocent victims and other civil losses resulting from this war. 
  The responsible source in the DRY Armed Forces Command 
confirmed that our ground defenses succeeded in shooting down 
one of the missiles, while another fell into the sea without 
causing any material damage (?or) [word indistinct]. [passage 
omitted]. 

</TEXT>

