<H3> <TI>   Military Operations, Battle Progress Reported </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Military Operations, Battle Progress Reported </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Northern Soldiers Urged To Surrender </H4>

<F P=102> EA2605191594 Aden Democratic Republic of Yemen Radio Network 
in English 1600 GMT 26 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA2605191594 </F>
<F P=104>  Aden Democratic Republic of Yemen Radio Network 
in English 1600 GMT 26 May 94 </F>

<F P=105> English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] An official source in the Command of the Armed 
Forces in democratic Yemen has given a statement saying that a 
number of soldiers and officers who surrendered at various 
battlefronts and who had been launched by the killer 'Ali 
'Abdallah Salih to fight against their brothers in the 
Democratic Republic of Yemen [DRY], have affirmed that their 
command had misinformed them about the facts on the political 
and military situations. For example, they informed them in Bab 
al-Mandeb-Kharaz axis that their forces had reached Salah al-Din 
camp, while those soldiers and officers at al- Rahidah front and 
Karish that their forces had reached Dar Sa'd on the outskirts 
of Aden. [sentence as heard] This was not only a deceit and 
misleading to these soldiers and officers in order to plunge 
them in fierce battles, but was against all reason. 
  The military source added that scientific military 
calculations do not accept this. There was also another fact 
which was ignored by the military command in Sanaa. It was that 
they were waging an aggressive war, which should be firmly 
countered by well-trained forces and by people who do not submit 
to any injustice and tyrant. The aggressors were faced with a 
brave resistance and incredible steadfastness on the part of the 
DRY's forces, which enjoy high morale and rare heroism. 
  The military source added that the democratic Yemen's Armed 
Forces Command in defense of the national and human 
responsibility towards the misled elements who were plunged by 
the al-Ahmar gang, calls on all these soldiers and officers to 
take a brave and reasonable stand and refuse to continue in this 
failed war into which they were launched by the family, which is 
concerned only to maintain the throne of authority of 'Ali 
'Abdallah Salih and his adventurous gang. The source expressed 
confidence of the Armed Forces of the DRY that these 
(?mischievous) elements will take any opportunity to get rid of 
the certain death and rid our people and their families of 
sadness and concern over their lives to which Sanaa's rulers 
give no consideration. The Armed Forces Command of the DRY 
affirm that those who will surrender spontaneously will receive 
all appreciation and respect from their brothers in blood and 
faith and affiliation to the sons of the DRY. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

