<DOCNO> FBIS4-60662 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drnes103_j_94031" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-NES-94-103 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  26 May 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Military Operations, Battle Progress Reported </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Military Operations, Battle Progress Reported </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Aden Notes Successes on Abyan Front </H4>

<F P=102> EA2605192194 Aden Democratic Republic of Yemen Radio Network 
in English 1600 GMT 26 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA2605192194 </F>
<F P=104>  Aden Democratic Republic of Yemen Radio Network 
in English 1600 GMT 26 May 94 </F>

<F P=105> English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Armed Forces Command has issued the military 
communique No. 27, saying that our armed forces today continued 
their crushing blows on the invading forces at all battlefronts, 
particularly in Abyan Governorate and in 
al-Anad-Karish-al-Rahidah axis. The communique said that our 
forces in Abyan continued their offensive operations as suicidal 
forces stormed the strongholds of these forces. The total 
estimates of these operations were destruction of six tanks, two 
missile vehicles, and that five tanks were captured by our 
forces. 

