<H3> <TI>   Sharon Announces Plan To Run for Prime Minister </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Sharon Announces Plan To Run for Prime Minister </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA2705045194 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in English 0400 GMT 27 
May 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2705045194 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Likud Knesset Member Ari'el Sharon says he has 
decided to bid for the premiership in the next elections. He 
says he is working to set up a national coalition which will 
include a number of personalities and groups. He mentioned in 
particular the Likud's former foreign minister, David Levi. 
  In an interview with Qol Yisra'el, Sharon also said that he 
was not leaving the Likud party as part of his bid for a 
leadership role. He hoped there would be primaries to head the 
national coalition. 

</TEXT>

