<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Netanyahu, Begin, Eytan React </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Netanyahu, Begin, Eytan React </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA2705063894 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 0500 GMT 27 
May 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2705063894 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Likud chairman Binyamin Netanyahu has harshly 
reacted to Ari'el Sharon's announcement that he intends to run 
for the premiership in the next elections and called on him to 
leave the Likud. Interviewed by Qol Yisra'el, Netanyahu said 
that Sharon sows conflict and dispute. He conspired against 
Menahem Begin and Yitzhaq Shamir and is now trying to conspire 
against me. The time has come for this intriguer to leave the 
Likud. All Sharon does is undermine, sabotage, and split, 
Netanyahu said. With him, this is a chronic disease. He is a 
man who does not recognize any democratic norms and sets out to 
destroy every framework, the Likud chairman asserted. 
  Sharon told our correspondent Hayim Hecht that he has been 
holding contacts to set up a united front of the right-wing camp 
which would hold primaries before the next elections and decide 
on its candidate. 
  Knesset Member Binyamin Begin told Qol Yisra'el that 
Sharon's 
chances of winning are similar to his chances of becoming the 
world's tennis champion. This is a wrong move which will lead 
to a split in the national camp, Begin said. 
  Tzomet leader Refa'el Eytan said he would run against 
Sharon. 
In his opinion, it could be an advantage if a few candidates of 
the national camp ran in the first round of elections. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

