<F P=100> Libya </F>
<H3> <TI>   Al-Qadhdhafi Holds Further Contacts With Yemenis </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Al-Qadhdhafi Holds Further Contacts With Yemenis </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2405143594 Tripoli JANA in English 1424 GMT 24 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2405143594 </F>
<F P=104>  Tripoli JANA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tripoli, al Maa' [May] 24, JAMAHIRIYAH NEWS AGENCY 
-- Successive phone calls were underway throughout the 'Aid al 
Adhah ['Id al-Adha] holiday between the leader of the revolution 
and the Yemeni leaders 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih and 'Ali Salim 
al-Bid in the ongoing efforts by the leader to bring an end to 
the suffering and destruction in Yemen. Over the last 24 hours 
telephone calls were exchanged between the various parties with 
the leader emphasizing the stance adopted by the Arab world and 
its revolutionary forces vis a vis division and those who 
support division. The leader said that it did not suit the 
revolutionaries of Aden to be in favour of division. 
  However, 'Ali Salim al-Bid explained to the leader of the 
revolution the reasons for his decision to break away but also 
expressed his willingness to search for any way out of the 
current sitution to restore the unity of Yemen even if at his 
expense. 
  The contacts made with 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih revolved mainly 
around a search for a political solution which would guarantee 
Yemeni unity, which would bring an end to the fighting and 
prevent further bloodshed. 

</TEXT>

