<H3> <TI>   JANA Editor Views Remarks by Clinton Adviser </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    JANA Editor Views Remarks by Clinton Adviser </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2505154194 Tripoli JANA in English 1443 GMT 25 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2505154194 </F>
<F P=104>  Tripoli JANA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tripoli, Al Maa' [May] 25, JAMAHIRIYAH NEWS AGENCY-- 
The international editor of the Jamahiriyah News Agency 
commented on the lecture given by Anthony Lake, the national 
security adviser to the American president, to the Institute of 
Middle Eastern Policy on the 17th of Al Maa'[May] which 
reaffirmed the American policy of domination in the Arab region 
as well as the basis for this policy which revolves around 
attempts to dominate the resources of the region while 
guaranteeing the security of the Israeli occupiers who are a 
tool for American imperialist policy in the region. 
  The editor said that the comments by the advisor to the 
American president demonstrated the mad frenzy of the 
imperialists resulting from their military domination of the 
world. The editor said that the ideas which came out in this 
lecture truly expresses the new wave of colonialism, occupation 
and invasion which has prevailed. He said this showed that there 
was a dreary future on the horizon which threatens peace, 
security and stability and will abort the peaceful process of 
development of all nations. 

</TEXT>

