<H3> <TI>   Musa Receives Delegation of U.S. Editors </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Musa Receives Delegation of U.S. Editors </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2605164794 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1328 GMT 26 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2605164794 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 26 May (MENA) -- Foreign Minister 'Amr Musa 
today received the delegation from the American Association of 
Chief Editors of Newspapers and Magazines. The delegation 
includes 14 chief editors and publishers representing some of 
the major newspapers in the United States. 
  The meeting dealt with Egyptian-U.S. relations, Egypt's 
leading role in the area, and the important role it is playing 
in the peace process to achieve stability and security in the 
area. 
  It also dealt with the implementation of the Gaza-Jericho 
agreement between the Palestinians and Israelis, which is 
considered a step toward achieving Palestinian-Israeli peace. 
  The meeting also dealt with the recent developments in Yemen 
and the Egyptian and U.S. efforts to stop the fighting and 
restart the dialogue between the Yemeni parties. 

</TEXT>

