<F P=102>   NC2505122294 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1015 GMT 25 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2505122294 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 25 May (MENA) -- Petroleum Minister Hamdi 
al-Banbi and a technical delegation left Cairo for Damascus 
today on a three-day official visit to Syria. 
  Al-Banbi said before leaving that he would discuss with his 
Syrian counterpart, Nadir Nabulsi, ways to boost technical 
cooperation in the field of petroleum industries and a project 
for a joint Egyptian-Syrian company for digging and maintaining 
oil wells. 
  He said Egyptian petrochemical industries will be exported 
to 
Syria. 

</TEXT>

