  [Text] Khartoum, 26 May (SUNA) -- Sudan has expressed its 
condemnation of all attempts at division and fragmentation and 
the lies of the advocates of the right to self-determination for 
illusory racial entities. 
  The Foreign Ministry said in a statement issued yesterday to 
mark the 31st anniversary of the OAU's establishment, that the 
anniversary comes at a time when the continent is becoming 
marginalized as part of the so-called new world order. It 
called for more solidarity, vigilance, and unity in the face of 
the conspiracies being hatched against the African continent. 

