<F P=100> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   Protesters Urge `Overthrow' of Hashemi-Rafsanjani </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Protesters Urge `Overthrow' of Hashemi-Rafsanjani </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM2605143994 London AL-HAYAH in Arabic 26 May 94 p 4 </F>
<F P=103> PM2605143994 </F>
<F P=104>  London AL-HAYAH </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Safa Ha'eri: "Demonstrations in Qom Against </F>
Khamene'i and Hashemi-Rafsanjani"] 
  [Text] Paris -- Anti-regime demonstrations involving some 
6,000 people were staged in Qom yesterday. Sources in the city 
said that the demonstrators, most of whom are clients and 
depositors of the "Waliyy ol-Asr" loans and savings company, 
which was established in 1991 by senior clerics, protested 
against the "disappearance" of some 12 billion riyals they had 
deposited in the company. Demonstrators chanted slogans, 
calling for the overthrow of 'Ali Khamene'i, the republic's 
guide, and President Hashemi-Rafsanjani. It is worth noting 
that, in the absence of a sound banking system, loans and 
savings companies thrived rapidly as a result of the interest 
rates they offer their clients. But most of these companies, 
which were established with the blessings of clerics, have 
become bankrupt quickly. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

