<F P=100> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   Visit of Turkmenistan's Niyazov Reported </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Visit of Turkmenistan's Niyazov Reported </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Meets With Hashemi-Rafsanjani </H4>

<F P=102> LD2605144794 Tehran IRIB Television First Program Network in 
Persian 1130 GMT 26 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2605144794 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRIB Television First Program Network </F>
<F P=105>  Persian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] President Hashemi-Rafsanjani, heading a 
high-ranking delegation, arrived in Mashhad this morning to meet 
the president of Turkmenistan. [passage omitted] During a 
meeting held at midday today, the two countries' presidents and 
their delegations met and reviewed ways of expanding ties and 
cooperation between Iran and Turkmenistan in the fields of 
transport, customs, banking, growth of commercial transactions, 
provision of facilities for goods transit, and cross border 
visits by the two countries' citizens. [video shows arrival and 
meeting with Saparmurad Niyazov] 
  During these talks, referring to the large and well-equipped 
Razavi commercial center currently under construction in 
Sarakhs, President Hashemi-Rafsanjani expressed the hope that 
when this trade center opens, the volume of transactions would 
increase between the merchants in both countries, among other 
neighboring countries and the rest of the region. 
  Niyazov too, during his remarks, in part referring to the 
growing volume of trade between the two countries, agreed with 
the export of cotton from Turkmenistan to Iran. In another part 
of his remarks, referring to the policy to expand road and 
railway networks between the two countries, Niyazov added: Good 
progress is made in the feasibility study phase of the project 
to transport Turkmenistan gas to Europe via Iran. 
  It is worth mentioning that at the conclusion of the talks 
between the presidents of the Islamic Republic of Iran and 
Turkmenistan it was agreed that ministers and expert teams from 
the two countries should study and investigate ways of 
strengthening bilateral cooperation and should inform their 
respective presidents on the outcome of their discussions. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

