<H3> <TI>   Visit of Turkmenistan's Niyazov Reported </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Visit of Turkmenistan's Niyazov Reported </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Inaugurates Mashhad Consulate </H4>

<F P=102> LD2605185794 Tehran IRNA in English 1837 GMT 26 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2605185794 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Mashhad (Khorasan) May 26, IRNA -- The presidents of 
Iran and Turkmenistan inaugurated the Turkmen consulate here 
Thursday. 
  The visiting Turkmen president, Saparmurad Niyazov, lauded 
the development saying that due to President 'Ali Akbar 
Hashemi-Rafsanjani's personal efforts, relations between Iran 
and his country have seen a steady progress. 
  Hojjat ol-Eslam Rafsanjani, too, was also pleased about the 
inauguration of the Turkmen consulate here and said both 
countries place an emphasis on their mutual relations. 
  A group of cabinet ministers of both countries were present 
at the inaugural ceremonies. The Islamic Republic opened its 
consulate in Marv of Turkmenistan earlier this year. 

</TEXT>

