<F P=100> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   Visit of Turkmenistan's Niyazov Reported </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Visit of Turkmenistan's Niyazov Reported </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Joint Communique Issued </H4>

<F P=102> LD2605201494 Tehran IRIB Television Second Program Network 
in Persian 1800 GMT 26 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2605201494 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRIB Television Second Program Network 
in Persian 1800 GMT 26 May 94 </F>

<F P=105> Persian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Following today's meeting between the presidents of 
the Islamic Republic of Iran and Turkmenistan, a joint 
communique was issued this evening. Part of the communique 
says: The presidents of the two countries held negotiations in 
a climate full of friendship, fraternity, and understanding, 
which is indicative of the good neighborly relations between the 
two countries. They exchanged views on political, economic, and 
cultural issues of mutual interest. Both sides have expressed 
their satisfaction at the agreements reached. 
  Cooperation in the oil and gas sector was high on the agenda 
of these talks. Both sides emphasized their support for the 
implementation of the project to transport gas from Turkmenistan 
to Europe via the Islamic Republic of Iran. 
  Both sides regarded cooperation in the field of transport as 
the main axis for the expansion of economic and trade relations 
between the countries. Expressing happiness at the move toward 
implementation of the Mashhad-Sarakhs railway line and the roads 
linking Quchan-Imamqoli, Dar-e Gaz-Imamqoli-Bajgiran, and 
Artiq-Lotfabad, the two sides called for the speeding up and 
completion of these projects. 
  Both sides also stressed the need to activate banking 
relations, establish agency [kargozary] relations, and to 
inaugurate a special account [hesab-e makhsus]. 
  Mr. Niyazov further thanked the government and people of the 
Islamic Republic of Iran for the warm welcome accorded to him. 
He invited Mr. Hashemi-Rafsanjani to visit Turkmenistan. The 
invitation was warmly accepted. 

</TEXT>

