<F P=100> India </F>
<H3> <TI>   President Leaves on Visit to Bulgaria, Romania </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    President Leaves on Visit to Bulgaria, Romania </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2605043194 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 0245 
GMT 26 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2605043194 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi All India Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The president, Dr. Shankar Dayal Sharma, has left 
New Delhi today on an eight-day state visit to Bulgaria and 
Romania. A high-level delegation, including the home minister, 
Mr. S.B. Chavan, and the civil aviation minister, Mr. Ghulam 
Nabi Azad, and ministers of state, Mr. Arvind Netam and Mr. 
Salman Kurshid, are accompanying the president. Our 
correspondent accompanying the president reports that the visit 
will explore the possibility of strengthening cooperation 
between India and the two East European countries. 
  The president was seen off at the airport by the vice 
president, Mr. K.R. Narayanan; the prime minister, Mr. P.V. 
Narasimha Rao; his cabinet colleagues; the Uttar Pradesh 
governor, Mr. Motilal Vora; and the three service chiefs. 
  In Bulgaria, six bilateral agreements are to be signed 
including one on avoidance of double taxation. The highlight of 
the president's visit to Romania will be adoption of a basic 
political document by the two countries. The president will 
also address a joint session of the Romanian senate and the 
chamber of deputies. The University of Bucharest is to confer an 
honorary doctorate on Dr. Shankar Dayal Sharma. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

