<H3> <TI>   ASEAN Asked To Help Develop `Global Trading System' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    ASEAN Asked To Help Develop `Global Trading System' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2505091194 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 0245 
GMT 25 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2505091194 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi All India Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] India has sought the cooperation of ASEAN -- the 
Association of South East Asian Nations -- for adopting a common 
strategy to evolve a nondiscriminatory global trading system. 
The commerce minister, Mr. Pranab Mukherjee, has said that the 
strategy will bridge the trade gap between the developing and 
the developed countries with the World Trade Organization coming 
into effect from January next. 

</TEXT>

