<F P=100> LEBANON </F>
<H3> <TI>   Buwayz Briefed on Christopher Mideast Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Buwayz Briefed on Christopher Mideast Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM2405103994 London AL-HAYAH in Arabic 21 May 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> PM2405103994 </F>
<F P=104>  London AL-HAYAH </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Buwayz: Syrian-Israeli Talks Have </F>
Not Reached Points of Agreement"] 
  [Excerpt] Beirut, AL-HAYAH -- Foreign Minister Faris 
Buwayz received a message from the U.S. Department of State 
yesterday. It was conveyed by U.S. Charge d'Affaires in Lebanon 
Vincent Battle. It deals with the outcome of Secretary of State 
Warren Christopher's recent talks in the Middle East on 
reactivating the Syrian-Israeli negotiation track. 
  Buwayz said that "the Syrian-Israeli-U.S. talks are still 
remote from the possibility of quickly reaching points of 
agreement, even though they are serious and broaching 
fundamental issues." He expected "further rounds of talks to be 
held before a call for resuming the negotiations crystallizes." 
  He described the "view that settling the Syrian file is 
bound 
to reflect positively on the Lebanese and Jordanian file as 
realistic." 
  He stressed that contacts are continuing between Beirut and 
Damascus, "and we are closely following what is happening with 
regard to the Syrian-Israeli negotiations. And if necessary, 
direct meetings (between Lebanon and Syria) are not difficult to 
hold." [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

