<F P=100> IRAQ </F>
<H3> <TI>   NPPF's 'Abd-al-Ghafur Criticizes al-Bid </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    NPPF's 'Abd-al-Ghafur Criticizes al-Bid </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN2605165994 Baghdad INA in Arabic 1545 GMT 26 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN2605165994 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad INA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Baghdad, 26 May (INA) -- 'Abd-al-Ghani 
'Abd-al-Ghafur, secretary general of the National Progressive 
and Patriotic Front [NPPF], has stressed that the NPPF and its 
parties support the unity of the Yemeni territory and people as 
a pan-Arab achievement, not only for Yemen but also for the Arab 
nation's masses. 
  In a statement to INA, 'Abd-al-Ghafur said the declaration 
by 
'Ali Salim al-Bid and his secessionist clique on setting up a 
deformed secessionist entity has only revealed the dimensions of 
the conspiracy and schemes hostile to both Yemeni unity and the 
Arab nation's hopes. 
  He indicated that Arab Iraq stands against the enemies of 
both the nation and its awakening. Iraq raised the slogans of 
Arab unity, of the liberation of Palestine, and of independent 
will. Iraq fought for these slogans in the historic and 
immortal Mother of Battles. 
  'Abd-al-Ghafur added that the NPPF parties wish the Yemeni 
people happiness and stability throughout their unified land. 
He noted that the NPPF general secretariat salutes the concern 
of the Yemeni people, national parties, and Armed Forces to 
preserve Yemeni unity and to confront the secessionists and 
their evil schemes. These schemes are implemented with support 
from the enemies of the nation, the imperialists, Zionists, and 
reactionaries, he added. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

