<F P=100> IRAQ </F>
<H3> <TI>   Speaker Salih Meets With Japanese Party Delegation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Speaker Salih Meets With Japanese Party Delegation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN2605163394 Baghdad INA in Arabic 1450 GMT 26 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN2605163394 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad INA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Baghdad, 26 May (INA) -- National Assembly Speaker 
Sa'di Mahdi Salih today received Masatu Okita, the higher 
adviser of the Social Democratic Party of Japan [SDPJ], and the 
accompanying delegation [name and title as received]. 
  During the meeting, Salih stressed Iraq's desire to 
establish 
strong friendship and cooperation relations with Japan. He said 
the return of Iraqi-Japanese relations to normal is necessary in 
order to achieve the interests of both friendly peoples in a way 
that benefits both countries. 
  Salih indicated the importance of promoting Iraqi-Japanese 
relations in the current and coming phases. He said Japan can 
play a greater role in this regard by making efforts to lift the 
blockade imposed on the Iraqi people, especially since Japan 
enjoys the international status entitling it to play such a role. 
  Okita emphasized the SDPJ's desire to promote Japanese-Iraqi 
relations on the official and party levels in a way that would 
achieve the interests of both friendly peoples. He said: We 
are working to establish a just, comprehensive, and lasting 
peace in the Arab region, avoiding the use of force. 
  Okita appreciated Iraq's peaceful positions and its call for 
the establishment of such a peace, so general welfare can be 
achieved for all regional states and also for friendly states. 
  The Japanese delegation arrived in Iraq yesterday on a visit 
lasting several days. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

